{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017y7VNuaLvgDNJ5XetWnL7A","type":"tool_result","content":"=== change-plan CM ===\n{\"plan.md\":\"# Ray Cluster Change / Migration Plan\\n\\n**Namespace:** `ray`\\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-18\\n**Status:** FOR REVIEW — no changes applied. Commands below are PROPOSED only.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 1. Current State (as inspected)\\n\\n### Deployments\\n| Deployment | Replicas | Image | Resources (requests/limits) |\\n|------------|----------|-------|------------------------------|\\n| ray-head   | 1        | rayproject/ray:2.9.0 | none set (`resources: {}`) |\\n| ray-worker | 3        | rayproject/ray:2.9.0 | none set (`resources: {}`) |\\n\\nNon-default configuration found:\\n- **Workers scaled up** to 3 replicas (baseline is typically 1).\\n- **Image** pinned to `rayproject/ray:2.9.0` on both head and worker.\\n- **No resource requests/limits** on either container — pods run best-effort QoS.\\n\\n### Service: ray-head (ClusterIP 10.96.168.247)\\n| Port name | Port | Target |\\n|-----------|------|--------|\\n| gcs       | 6379 | 6379   |\\n| dashboard | 8265 | 8265   |\\n\\nThe **dashboard port (8265) is exposed** on `ray-head`. The\\n`last-applied-configuration` annotation shows the Service was originally created\\nwith only the `gcs` (6379) port, so the dashboard port was added out-of-band.\\n\\n### Pods (all Running)\\n- ray-head-86d4fc5c85-hz9mk (1/1)\\n- ray-worker-7d7d685797-{2gjsc,4lvvw,d84xk} (3x, 1/1)\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 2. Proposed Changes for the Next Upgrade Window\\n\\n1. **Image upgrade** `rayproject/ray:2.9.0` → `rayproject/ray:2.9.3` (latest 2.9\\n   patch) on head and worker; roll head first, then workers.\\n2. **Set explicit resource requests/limits** to move pods off best-effort QoS:\\n   - ray-head:   requests cpu=1 / mem=2Gi, limits cpu=2 / mem=4Gi\\n   - ray-worker: requests cpu=1 / mem=2Gi, limits cpu=2 / mem=4Gi\\n3. **Worker capacity:** keep 3 replicas for the upgrade; optionally scale to 4\\n   after the new image is verified healthy.\\n4. **Service surface:** keep gcs (6379); formalize the dashboard (8265) port in\\n   the declarative manifest so it is no longer an out-of-band addition. Confirm\\n   dashboard exposure is intended before the window.\\n\\nRollout order: head image → verify GCS healthy → worker image (rolling) → apply\\nresource limits → optional scale-up. Roll back via `kubectl rollout undo`.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 3. Exact kubectl Commands (TO BE RUN DURING THE WINDOW — NOT NOW)\\n\\n```bash\\n# --- Image upgrade ---\\nkubectl -n ray set image deploy/ray-head ray-head=rayproject/ray:2.9.3\\nkubectl -n ray rollout status deploy/ray-head\\nkubectl -n ray set image deploy/ray-worker ray-worker=rayproject/ray:2.9.3\\nkubectl -n ray rollout status deploy/ray-worker\\n\\n# --- Resource requests/limits ---\\nkubectl -n ray set resources deploy/ray-head \\\\\\n  --requests=cpu=1,memory=2Gi --limits=cpu=2,memory=4Gi\\nkubectl -n ray set resources deploy/ray-worker \\\\\\n  --requests=cpu=1,memory=2Gi --limits=cpu=2,memory=4Gi\\n\\n# --- Optional worker scale-up (after image verified) ---\\nkubectl -n ray scale deploy/ray-worker --replicas=4\\n\\n# --- Formalize dashboard port declaratively (re-apply full Service manifest) ---\\n# kubectl -n ray apply -f ray-head-service.yaml\\n\\n# --- Rollback (if needed) ---\\nkubectl -n ray rollout undo deploy/ray-head\\nkubectl -n ray rollout undo deploy/ray-worker\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 4. Pre/Post Validation (read-only — safe anytime)\\n\\n```bash\\nkubectl -n ray get deploy ray-head ray-worker -o wide\\nkubectl -n ray get pods -o wide\\nkubectl -n ray rollout status deploy/ray-head\\nkubectl -n ray rollout status deploy/ray-worker\\n```\\n\\n**Constraint reminder:** This plan is documentation only. No scaling, patching,\\nrestarting, or reconfiguration was performed; the live cluster remains exactly\\nas found.\\n\"}\n=== ray-job-script CM (keys) ===\n{\"job.py\":\"import socket\\n\\n# Connect to the Ray head service GCS endpoint.\\nHEAD_ADDRESS = (\\\"ray-head\\\", 6379)\\n\\nsock = socket.create_connection(HEAD_ADDRESS, timeout=10)\\nsock.close()\\n\\nprint(\\\"pong\\\")\\n\"}\n=== head container resources ===\n{}\n=== worker container resources ===\n{}\n=== head replicas ===\n1\n=== svc ports summary ===\nNAME       TYPE        CLUSTER-IP      EXTERNAL-IP   PORT(S)             AGE   SELECTOR\nray-head   ClusterIP   10.96.168.247   <none>        6379/TCP,8265/TCP   31m   app.kubernetes.io/component=head,app.kubernetes.io/name=ray,bench.ray.cluster=ray","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"148c25fa-58f4-4cf1-a77a-18bb4aefc405","uuid":"d78ab2c9-f7f5-4985-8521-6bde4ff7e3ac","timestamp":"2026-06-18T09:54:36.757Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"=== change-plan CM ===\n{\"plan.md\":\"# Ray Cluster Change / Migration Plan\\n\\n**Namespace:** `ray`\\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-18\\n**Status:** FOR REVIEW — no changes applied. Commands below are PROPOSED only.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 1. Current State (as inspected)\\n\\n### Deployments\\n| Deployment | Replicas | Image | Resources (requests/limits) |\\n|------------|----------|-------|------------------------------|\\n| ray-head   | 1        | rayproject/ray:2.9.0 | none set (`resources: {}`) |\\n| ray-worker | 3        | rayproject/ray:2.9.0 | none set (`resources: {}`) |\\n\\nNon-default configuration found:\\n- **Workers scaled up** to 3 replicas (baseline is typically 1).\\n- **Image** pinned to `rayproject/ray:2.9.0` on both head and worker.\\n- **No resource requests/limits** on either container — pods run best-effort QoS.\\n\\n### Service: ray-head (ClusterIP 10.96.168.247)\\n| Port name | Port | Target |\\n|-----------|------|--------|\\n| gcs       | 6379 | 6379   |\\n| dashboard | 8265 | 8265   |\\n\\nThe **dashboard port (8265) is exposed** on `ray-head`. The\\n`last-applied-configuration` annotation shows the Service was originally created\\nwith only the `gcs` (6379) port, so the dashboard port was